   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["Formed from Margaret."]}]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":10,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":0},{"id":1705193,"age":19,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret d'Arden was born in 1318, in England, her father, Sir Robert d'Arderne, was 78 and her mother, Nicola Bardolf, was 25. She had at least 1 son with Sir Nicholas Peyvre 3rd Baron Peyvre. She died in 1379, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1318–1379":"1318–1379","1315–Female":"1315–Surnud","1330–1376":"1330–1376","1318–1361":"1318–1361","1352–1429":"1352–1429","1240–1331":"1240–1331","1294–1365":"1294–1365","1352":"1352","1330":"1330","1240":"1240","1361":"1361","1294":"1294","13 September 1361":"13. september 1361","1337":"1337","1315":"1315","1379":"1379","1365":"1365","1453":"1453","1376":"1376","1331":"1331","about 1331":"umbes 1331","1429":"1429","1318":"1318","1328":"1328","Toddington